==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tribunitian
<hw>Trib`u*ni*tian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>tribunicius</ets>, <ets>tribunitius</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>tribunitien</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to tribunes;
befitting a tribune; <as>as, <ex>tribunitial</ex> power or
authority</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A kind of <qex>tribunician</qex> veto, forbidding that which is
recognized to be wrong.</q> <rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tribunitious</ent>⟦br⟧
